[171.67912, "o", "\u001b[0m\u001b[7;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[8;1H\u001b[2K                                                                            \u001b[2m3 calls │ 64,943 tokens │ $0.2053\u001b[0m\u001b[9;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[10;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[1m\u001b[96m\u001b[100m❯ Delegate to the explore-agent to map this project's structure — what each file and function does and how\u001b[11;1H\u001b[2K  they fit together — then report its findings back to me.\u001b[0m\u001b[12;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 1 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(22086 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(7.9s)\u001b[0m\u001b[13;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mThe user wants me to delegate the project-mapping task to an explore-agent. I should first discover \u001b[0m\u001b[14;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mthe explore-agent tool before invoking it. Searching the agent registry for \"explore\".\u001b[0m\u001b[15;1H\u001b[2K  \u001b[36m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1;36mlist-tools\u001b[0m({\"pattern\" \"explore\", \"type\" \"agent\"}): called \u001b[2m→\u001b[0m \u001b[92mdone\u001b[0m, 2ms, 4.6k chars\u001b[16;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 2 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(23989 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(38.5s)\u001b[0m\u001b[17;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mIteration 1 already disc"]
