[378.910301, "o", " 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(21287 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(6.4s)\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mStep 1 of the task is to list the project's files with bash. I'll list files excluding the \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2m.brainyard directory to keep it relevant. Next iteration I'll read src/cli.py.\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[36m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1;36mbash\u001b[0m({\"command\" \"find . -type f -not -path './.brainyard/*' -n...): called \u001b[2m→\u001b[0m \u001b[92mdone\u001b[0m, 22ms, 89 chars\r\n\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 2 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(21464 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(5.5s)\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mFiles are listed: README.md, src/cli.py, src/util.py. Now I need to read src/cli.py to summarize \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mwhat the CLI does and its flags.\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[36m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1;36mread-file\u001b[0m({\"path\" \"src/cli.py\"}): called \u001b[2m→\u001b[0m \u001b[92mdone\u001b[0m, 2ms, 706 chars\r\n\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 3 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(22192 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(8.2s)\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mThe task had two steps, both done: (1) bash listed the files (README.md, src/cli.py, src/util.py), \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b["]
[378.91038, "o", "2mand (2) read-file returned the contents of src/cli.py. The file defines a tiny argparse CLI named \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2m\"greet\" with one positional argument and one optional flag. I have everything needed to answer.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[92m┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mProject Files\u001b[0m                                                              \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m   • \u001b[36mREADME.md\u001b[0m                                                              \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m   • \u001b[36msrc/cli.py\u001b[0m                                                             \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m   • \u001b[36msrc/util.py\u001b[0m                                                            \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m                                                                            \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[9"]
[378.9104, "o", "2m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97m`src/cli.py` Summary\u001b[0m                                                       \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m A tiny Python CLI named \u001b[1;97m\u001b[36mgreet\u001b[0m\u001b[0m that prints a greeting.                      \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m                                                                            \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m   • Parses arguments with \u001b[36margparse\u001b[0m                                         \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m   • Delegates greeting formatting to \u001b[36mformat_greeting\u001b[0m (imported from \u001b[36mutil\u001b[0m)  \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m   • Prints the result to stdout                                            \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m                                                                            \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mArguments / Flags\u001b[0m                                                          \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mArgument\u001b[0m\u001b[2m │ \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mType\u001b[0m                      \u001b[2m │ \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mDescription\u001b[0m                   "]
